# ============================================================================
# SAGE AUTH SERVICE - ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
#
# This project supports environment-specific configurations:
#
#   DEVELOPMENT: Uses LocalStack to mock AWS services locally
#   PRODUCTION:  Uses real AWS services and Supabase database
#
# ============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# ============================================================================
#
# For Development (LocalStack):
#   1. Copy .env.development.example to .env.development
#   2. Fill in your Google OAuth credentials
#   3. Run: docker-compose up --build
#
# For Production (AWS + Supabase):
#   1. Copy .env.production.example to .env.production
#   2. Fill in all production credentials (AWS, Supabase, etc.)
#   3. Set ENVIRONMENT=production in your deployment
#   4. Deploy to AWS Lambda
#
# ============================================================================
# QUICK START (Development):
# ============================================================================

ENVIRONMENT=development

# Security - Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-change-this-to-a-random-string

# Google OAuth2 - Get from https://console.cloud.google.com/
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret_here

# ============================================================================
# For complete configuration options, see:
#   - .env.development.example (LocalStack configuration)
#   - .env.production.example (AWS + Supabase configuration)
# ============================================================================